url: "https://avc.com/2013/05/the-bitcoin-ecosystem/"
pubDate: 2013-08-22
takeaway: "Venture capitalist Fred Wilson analyzes the emerging business and developer ecosystem around Bitcoin, highlighting how a decentralized protocol is enabling a new class of financial applications and services."
---

Reading Fred Wilson's 2013 thoughts on the Bitcoin ecosystem feels like looking at a blueprint of the modern web before the skyscrapers were built. Back then, most people still viewed Bitcoin as either an illegal currency or a brief speculative mania. Wilson, with a VC's eye for platform dynamics, saw something much deeper: a decentralized protocol that was rapidly turning into an open developer playground. He recognized that by stripping away the gatekeepers of traditional finance, Bitcoin was enabling a completely new class of financial applications and services that could be built and deployed globally without asking for permission.

As a founder, what stands out is how Wilson framed the protocol-as-a-platform thesis. In traditional tech, you build on top of APIs owned by giant corporations that can cut your access on a whim. Building on a decentralized protocol, however, guarantees a neutral foundation where the rules of the game can't be changed overnight. This creates massive incentives for developers to invest their time and capital into building durable services. This post reminds me that the most powerful waves of innovation occur when we lower the barrier to entry, allowing any developer with an internet connection to write financial code that executes globally.

### What stuck with me
* **Protocol as platform**: Decentralized protocols provide an un-censorable, neutral foundation for developers to build long-term applications without platform risk.
* **Permissionless financial innovation**: Removing centralized financial gatekeepers enables developers to experiment and deploy global services at a fraction of traditional costs.
* **Developer bootstrapping cycle**: A vibrant developer ecosystem is the primary driver of value and utility in any emerging decentralized network.
